<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hi everyone,</p> <p>There is a version 0.4 out for the <strong>dtache</strong> package. The short description of the package is that it provides the possibility to run commands that are detached from Emacs. To read more see the README here <a href="https://gitlab.com/niklaseklund/dtache">https://gitlab.com/niklaseklund/dtache</a>. The major changes compared to the last release is:</p> <ul> <li><strong>dtache</strong> now integrates with the built in <strong>notifications</strong> library and this is used as default now for all users</li> <li><strong>dtache</strong> now uses <strong>filenotify</strong> to monitor the decoupled processes. This is done for both local and remote commands.</li> <li><strong>dtache</strong> now fully supports users on <strong>macOS</strong></li> <li><strong>dtache</strong> now is pre-configured with bindings in its minor/major-modes in order to simplify configurations for the users</li> <li><strong>dtache</strong> is now available on <strong>ELPA</strong>, <strong>MELPA</strong> and as a <strong>Guix</strong> package</li> </ul> <p>ELPA: <a href="http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/dtache.html">http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/dtache.html</a></p> <p>MELPA: <a href="https://melpa.org/#/dtache">https://melpa.org/#/dtache</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/squirelpower"> /u/squirelpower </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/sbjy4o/dtache_version_04/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/sbjy4o/dtache_version_04/">[comments]</a></span>